Document: AnimationNodeStateMachineTransition
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodestatemachinetransition.rst
Summary: Defines the properties and behavior of a transition between states in an AnimationNodeStateMachine.

Inherits: Resource < Object

This class represents a transition between two states in an AnimationNodeStateMachine. It defines the conditions under which the transition occurs, such as by input, by time, or by a custom condition.

Properties:
- advance_condition (StringName): The name of the AnimationNodeStateMachine's input port that must be active to trigger this transition. If empty, the transition is triggered by time.
- advance_mode (int): The mode used to determine when the transition should occur. Possible values:
    - 0: Transition on time (default).
    - 1: Transition on input.
    - 2: Transition on condition.
- advance_wait_time (float): The time in seconds to wait before automatically transitioning to the next state when advance_mode is set to Transition on Time. Default: 0.0.
- delete_on_exit (bool): If true, the transition will be deleted from the state machine when it is no longer needed. Default: true.
- xfade_time (float): The time in seconds for the crossfade between the current animation and the next animation. Default: 0.0.

Methods:
- get_advance_condition() → StringName: Returns the name of the AnimationNodeStateMachine's input port that must be active to trigger this transition.
- set_advance_condition(condition: StringName) → void: Sets the name of the AnimationNodeStateMachine's input port that must be active to trigger this transition.
- get_advance_mode() → int: Returns the advance mode of the transition.
- set_advance_mode(mode: int) → void: Sets the advance mode of the transition.
- get_advance_wait_time() → float: Returns the time in seconds to wait before automatically transitioning to the next state.
- set_advance_wait_time(time: float) → void: Sets the time in seconds to wait before automatically transitioning to the next state.
- get_xfade_time() → float: Returns the crossfade time in seconds.
- set_xfade_time(time: float) → void: Sets the crossfade time in seconds.
- is_delete_on_exit() → bool: Returns true if the transition will be deleted when it is no longer needed.
- set_delete_on_exit(enable: bool) → void: Sets whether the transition will be deleted when it is no longer needed.
---CHUNK---
