Document: AnimationNodeStateMachineTransition
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodestatemachinetransition.rst
Summary: Defines the properties and enumerations for controlling transitions between states in an AnimationStateMachine.

Inherits: AnimationNode (AnimationNode)

Signals
advance_condition_changed()
Emitted when advance_condition is changed.

Enumerations
enum SwitchMode:
SWITCH_MODE_IMMEDIATE (0): Switch to the next state immediately. The current state will end and blend into the beginning of the new one.
SWITCH_MODE_SYNC (1): Switch to the next state immediately, but will seek the new state to the playback position of the old state.
SWITCH_MODE_AT_END (2): Wait for the current state playback to end, then switch to the beginning of the next state animation.

enum AdvanceMode:
ADVANCE_MODE_DISABLED (0): Don't use this transition.
ADVANCE_MODE_ENABLED (1): Only use this transition during AnimationNodeStateMachinePlayback.travel().
ADVANCE_MODE_AUTO (2): Automatically use this transition if the advance_condition and advance_expression checks are true (if assigned).
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimationNodeStateMachineTransition
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodestatemachinetransition.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of an AnimationNodeStateMachineTransition, which controls how transitions between states in an AnimationStateMachine occur.

Property Descriptions
advance_condition (StringName): Controls when a transition automatically occurs. When set, this string becomes a boolean parameter on the AnimationTree that can be controlled from code.
Method: set_advance_condition(value: StringName)
Method: get_advance_condition() -> StringName

advance_expression (String): Allows for complex, script-driven conditions for state machine transitions, offering greater flexibility.
Method: set_advance_expression(value: String)
Method: get_advance_expression() -> String

advance_mode (AdvanceMode): Determines how a transition is triggered. Options include disabled, enabled via travel(), or automatic traversal if conditions are met.
Method: set_advance_mode(value: AdvanceMode)
Method: get_advance_mode() -> AdvanceMode

break_loop_at_end (bool): If true, the transition will break the animation loop at the end of its cycle, even if the animation is set to loop. Default is false.
Method: set_break_loop_at_end(value: bool)
Method: is_loop_broken_at_end() -> bool

priority (int): Determines the preference for this transition when multiple transitions are possible. Lower priority values are preferred. Default is 1.
Method: set_priority(value: int)
Method: get_priority() -> int

reset (bool): If true, the destination animation will play from its beginning when this transition is made. Default is true.
Method: set_reset(value: bool)
Method: is_reset() -> bool

switch_mode (SwitchMode): Defines the type of transition.
Method: set_switch_mode(value: SwitchMode)
Method: get_switch_mode() -> SwitchMode

xfade_curve (Curve): A Curve resource used to control the easing of the cross-fade between animations. It should be a unit curve.
Method: set_xfade_curve(value: Curve)
Method: get_xfade_curve() -> Curve

xfade_time (float): The duration of the cross-fade between the current and next animation. Default is 0.0.
Note: The AnimationStateMachine transitions the current state immediately after fading begins. The exact remaining time depends on the main animation. The xfade_time is not scaled by downstream delta.
Method: set_xfade_time(value: float)
Method: get_xfade_time() -> float